    <h2>What is CriticalOS?</h2>
    <p>CriticalOS is a deterministic AI control system. It governs agents, memory, and logic beyond the limits of centralized model APIs. It is cryptographically verified and designed for use after AI regulation becomes enforced.</p><h2>Core Features</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Scoped Memory Layers</li>
  <li>Arbitration Kernel</li>
  <li>Prompt-Only Execution Shell</li>
  <li>Risk & Safety Validator</li>
  <li>Owner-Gated Contract Issuance (CCC)</li>
  <li>Cryptographic System Integrity Proof</li>
</ul>

<h2>Why It Matters</h2>
<p>As AI regulations tighten, traditional models will be restricted. CriticalOS provides sovereign execution logic, internal governance, and agent-level autonomy that meets compliance — without losing capability.</p>

